 Hundreds of friends family fans and high-profile dignitaries have gathered at the DJ Thomas Hall in Alberton to bid farewell to jazz legend Thandi Klaasen.Klaasen died at the age of 86 after a long battle with pancreatic cancer.The musician and political stelwart will be laid to rest at the Thomas Nkosi Memorial Park Heroes Acre in Boksburg.It has been an emotionally-charged service as those close to Klaasen fondly remembered the contribution she made to the country through music.High-profile personalities including former President Thabo Mbeki Dorothy Masuku Caiphus Semenya and Abigail Kubheka are at the service.Watch: She stood out and served selflessly 